if I have argocd then kubectl commands what is the use ?
--> "With ArgoCD, we avoid using kubectl for deployments.
We use kubectl only for observability and debugging â€” not for making permanent changes.
Git remains the single source of truth, and ArgoCD keeps the cluster in sync."
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"In a GitOps setup with ArgoCD, we should never use helm rollback.
Rollback must be done via Git revert or ArgoCD rollback based on Git revision.
ArgoCD ensures Git is always single source of truth."
